Linked Discourses 22
8. Itchy
74. Origin
At Sāvatthī.
“Mendicants, an uneducated ordinary person doesn’t truly understand the origin, the ending, the gratification, the drawback, and the escape when it comes to form,
feeling,
perception,
choices,
and consciousness.
An educated noble disciple does truly understand the origin, the ending, the gratification, the drawback, and the escape when it comes to form,
feeling,
perception,
choices,
and consciousness.”

